abstract: U.S. Attorney General William Barr is considering resigning over President Donald Trump's tweets about Justice Department investigations, a source familiar with the situation told Reuters, while the department said he was not leaving.
snippet: U.S. Attorney General William Barr is considering resigning over President Donald Trump's tweets about Justice Department investigations, a source familiar with the situation told Reuters, while the department said he was not leaving.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - U.S. Attorney General William Barr is considering resigning over President Donald Trump's tweets about Justice Department investigations, a source familiar with the situation told Reuters, while the department said he was not leaving.
headline_main: U.S. Attorney General Barr Considers Quitting Over Trump Tweets: Source
headline_print_headline: U.S. Attorney General Barr Considers Quitting Over Trump Tweets: Source

abstract: A billionaire faces a test as his moderate rivals scramble. This is your morning tip sheet.
snippet: A billionaire faces a test as his moderate rivals scramble. This is your morning tip sheet.
lead_paragraph: Senator Amy Klobuchar’s campaign bus was parked in a lot near the Trump Hotel in Las Vegas on Monday.

abstract: Michael Milken was among a “who’s who of white-collar criminals” given official reprieve by President Trump.
snippet: Michael Milken was among a “who’s who of white-collar criminals” given official reprieve by President Trump.
lead_paragraph: Mike Bloomberg will appear onstage for the first time at a Democratic debate tonight, and Senator Elizabeth Warren is ready: “Primary voters curious about how each candidate will take on Donald Trump can get a live demonstration of how we each take on an egomaniac billionaire,” she tweeted. abstract: Mike Bloomberg would sell the financial data and media company he created in the 1980s — which bears his name and made him a multibillionaire — if he is elected U.S. president, a top adviser said Tuesday.
snippet: Mike Bloomberg would sell the financial data and media company he created in the 1980s — which bears his name and made him a multibillionaire — if he is elected U.S. president, a top adviser said Tuesday.
lead_paragraph: SACRAMENTO, Calif. — Mike Bloomberg would sell the financial data and media company he created in the 1980s — which bears his name and made him a multibillionaire — if he is elected U.S. president, a top adviser said Tuesday.
headline_main: Bloomberg Would Sell Business Interests if Elected President
headline_print_headline: Bloomberg Would Sell Business Interests if Elected President

abstract: Iran’s foreign minister said Wednesday that he believes his recent meeting with a U.S. senator had spooked the Trump administration because it was an opportunity to talk directly to “the American nation.”
snippet: Iran’s foreign minister said Wednesday that he believes his recent meeting with a U.S. senator had spooked the Trump administration because it was an opportunity to talk directly to “the American nation.”
lead_paragraph: TEHRAN, Iran — Iran’s foreign minister said Wednesday that he believes his recent meeting with a U.S. senator had spooked the Trump administration because it was an opportunity to talk directly to “the American nation.”
headline_main: Iran's FM Says His Meeting With US Senator Spooked Trump
headline_print_headline: Iran's FM Says His Meeting With US Senator Spooked Trump

abstract: Michael Bloomberg faced a barrage of attacks at his first Democratic presidential debate on Wednesday, as his rivals rushed to criticize the billionaire businessman for his wealth, record on race and history of sexist comments.

lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — Michael Bloomberg faced a barrage of attacks at his first Democratic presidential debate on Wednesday, as his rivals rushed to criticize the billionaire businessman for his wealth, record on race and history of sexist comments.
headline_main: Bloomberg Comes Under Bruising Attack at Democratic Presidential Debate in Nevada
headline_print_headline: Bloomberg Comes Under Bruising Attack at Democratic Presidential Debate in Nevada

abstract: As Republican President Donald Trump seeks a second term in November, Americans' interest in voting is growing faster in large cities dominated by Democrats than in conservative rural areas, according to an analysis of Reuters/Ipsos national opinion polls.
snippet: As Republican President Donald Trump seeks a second term in November, Americans' interest in voting is growing faster in large cities dominated by Democrats than in conservative rural areas, according to an analysis of Reuters/Ipsos national opini...
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — As Republican President Donald Trump seeks a second term in November, Americans' interest in voting is growing faster in large cities dominated by Democrats than in conservative rural areas, according to an analysis of Reuters/Ipsos national opinion polls.
headline_main: Exclusive: Ahead of 2020 Election, a 'Blue Wave' Is Rising in the Cities, Polling Analysis Shows
headline_print_headline: Exclusive: Ahead of 2020 Election, a 'Blue Wave' Is Rising in the Cities, Polling Analysis Shows

abstract: India's cabinet on Wednesday approved a plan to sign an initial pact on intellectual property rights with the United States, a government minister said, days ahead of a visit by U.S. President Donald Trump.
snippet: India's cabinet on Wednesday approved a plan to sign an initial pact on intellectual property rights with the United States, a government minister said, days ahead of a visit by U.S. President Donald Trump.
lead_paragraph: NEW DELHI — India's cabinet on Wednesday approved a plan to sign an initial pact on intellectual property rights with the United States, a government minister said, days ahead of a visit by U.S. President Donald Trump.
headline_main: India Clears Accord on Intellectual Property Rights With U.S.
headline_print_headline: India Clears Accord on Intellectual Property Rights With U.S.
